xsd:string "The collection contains between 4,000 and 40,000 artifacts, though the exact count depends on how the artifacts are catalogued. According to Yale University, about 350 of these artifacts are of a high enough quality to display in a museum. The museum-quality artifacts are mostly ceramics, but also include silver and bronze objects, stoneware cooking implements, and several vases for storing corn beer, an important beverage in Incan daily life. The “research collection” also contains human remains, as well as ceramic fragments."
